  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN161-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">pirivuṇarttiya tōḻi talaimakaḷatu vēṟupāṭu kaṇṭu muṉṉamē uṇarntāḷ niṉcelaveṉṟu celavuvilakkiyatu. (C7: niṉcelavu muṉṉamē yuṇarntāḷ namperumāṭṭiyeṉṟu talaimakaṉaic celavuvilakkiyatu.)</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">How the confidante whom [HE] informed of the separation, upon seeing the changes in HER hindered [his] going by saying “even before she has understood your going”.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN161">
      <lg type="edition">
        <l>viṉaivayiṟ pirital yāvatu vaṇarcuri</l>
        <l>va<supplied>ṭi</supplied>yāp pittai vaṉka ṇāṭava</l>
        <l>raṭiyamai pakaḻi vāra vāṅki</l>
        <l>vampalarc cekutta vañcuvaru kavalaip</l>
        <l>paṭumu<supplied>ṭai</supplied> nacaiiya vāḻkaṭ ceñcevi</l>
        <l>yeruvaic cēva līṇṭukiḷai payirum</l>
        <l>veruvaru kāṉa nīntip poruḷpurin</l>
        <l>tiṟappa veṇṇiṉi reṉpatu ciṟappak</l>
        <l>kēṭṭaṉaḷ kollō tāṉē tōṭṭāḻpu</l>
        <l>curumpuṇa volivaru mirumpal kūnta</l>
        <l>lammā mēṉi yāyiḻaik kuṟumakaḷ</l>
        <l>cuṇaṅkucū ḻākat taṇaṅkeṉa vurutta</l>
        <l>nalvara liḷamulai naṉaiyap</l>
        <l>pallita ḻuṇkaṇ parantaṉa paṉiyē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>Parting for the sake of wealth, what is that? (1a-c)</l>
        <l>That you would consider to traverse [the desert], (8a-c)</l>
        <l>making a fortune, crossing the frightening forest, (7)</l>
        <l>where the male of the brahminy kite calls [its] gathering flock, (6)</l>
        <l>with red ears [and] lively eyes that yearn for the flesh falling (5)</l>
        <l>on the dreadful crossroads, where travellers are destroyed (4)</l>
        <l>by strong men with untidy tufts of curling hair, (1d-2)</l>
        <l>bending [their bows], while the arrows are lined up, feet still, (3)</l>
        <l>did she hear that with exultation, she? (8d-9)</l>
        <l>The little woman with choice jewels, a pretty dark body (11)</l>
        <l>[and] many dark tresses that hang down on [her] shoulders [and] sprout, for bees to feed, (9d-10)</l>
        <l>tears spread in her kajal eyes with many lashes (14)</l>
        <l>so that her well-grown young breasts become wet (13)</l>
        <l>that are shaped like [those of] an Aṇaṅku, [her] bosom surrounded with beauty spots. (12)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
